To map a domain name to an IPv4 address using Amazon Route 53 for AWS, you can create a record using the Route 53 resources. Here's the Terraform configuration for setting up an A record in Route 53:

```hcl
resource "aws_route53_zone" "example" {
  name = "example.com"
}

resource "aws_route53_record" "example" {
  zone_id = aws_route53_zone.example.id
  name    = "www"
  type    = "A"
  ttl     = "300"
  records = [
    {
      value = "192.0.2.44" // Replace with your actual IPv4 address
    },
  ]
}
```

In this configuration, an `aws_route53_zone` resource is first defined to create a hosted zone for the domain `example.com`. Then, an `aws_route53_record` resource is used to map the alias `www` to a specific IPv4 address. Adjust the `value` in the record to match your domain's IPv4 address.

