To create an AWS Lex bot using Terraform, you need to define an AWS Lex Bot resource using the AWS Lex module. Here's a Terraform configuration that aligns with the format provided in your examples:

```hcl
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-west-2" // Specify your desired region
}

resource "aws_lex_bot" "example_bot" {
  name    = "MyLexBot"
  description = "A sample Lex bot"
  role_arn    = "arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/service-role/AmazonLexRole"

  locale_configuration {
    locale   = "en-US"
    child_directed_landing_page = "https://example.com"
  }
}

resource "aws_lex_bot_alias" "example_bot_alias" {
  name    = "my-bot-alias"
  bot_id   = aws_lex_bot.example_bot.name
  bot_version = "1.0"
  bot_name = "MyLexBot"
  bot_locales {
    locale    = "en-US"
  }
}
```

This configuration includes the essential components of an Amazon Lex bot and bot alias. Adjust the `region` and `role_arn` to match your AWS configuration. The EFS file system id and KMS key should be configured appropriately if your Lex bot needs these features. Replace placeholders with actual values where necessary.

