In this configuration, an AWS Lex bot is created for ordering pizza. The bot has a specific name that includes a suffix generated by `random_id` and a password generated by `random_password` to ensure that each new bot created requires a unique name and configuration settings. The Lex bot is set up to handle the intent of ordering pizza, with slots for size and toppings, and includes prompts for when a user has not provided all their requested slots. It also utilizes a `CodeHook` for fulfillment, which allows you to route to AWS Lambda functions or any other code points during execution. 

Remember, you need to ensure that all back-end resources (like Lambda) and permissions in the AWS Lex setup are configured in accordance with the bot configuration.

