response:
To configure an OIDC identity provider for an AWS EKS cluster with the specified parameters, you can generate the following Terraform script. This script defines an AWS EKS cluster and sets up the OIDC identity provider using the provided parameters:

```hcl
resource "aws_eks_cluster" "example" {
  name     = "example"
  skip_tenant_creation = false
}

resource "aws_iam_open_id_connect_provider" "example_oidc" {
  url            = "https://oidc.example.com"
  client_id_list = ["example-oidc-client", "another-client-id"]
  thumbprint_list = ["01:0F:EA:00:39:42:9F:EA:2A:3B:CF:10:9D:11:10:22:42:83", "02:0F:EA:00:39:42:9F:EA:2A:3B:CF:10:9D:11:10:23:45:86"]

  # Example cluster link
  resource "aws_eks_cluster_identity_oidc_provider_config" "example" {
    managed_by_cluster    = true
    cluster = aws_eks_cluster.example
  }
}
```

This configuration sets up an OIDC identity provider with the specified parameters and links it to an AWS EKS cluster named "example" using certain OIDC handshake requirements such as `client_id_list` and `thumbprint_list`.

