In this configuration, `example` is a pod identity IAM policy document allowing an EKS pod to assume a specific role. The policy is attached to an IAM role, also named `example`, which is linked to the EKS service account in the association resource. The role `example` is further attached to an `aws_iam_policy` for S3 read-only access.

Make sure to replace placeholder values and identifiers with actual values appropriate for your use case, like `service_account` and `policy_arn`. This configuration uses Terraform resources to create, configure, and associate AWS IAM policies and roles with EKS pod identities, enabling AWS Kubernetes service IAM roles to assume roles for AWS services access.

