```hcl
resource "aws_sagemaker_pipeline" "example_pipeline" {
  name = "my-sagemaker-pipeline"

  role_arn = "arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/service-role/my-sagemaker-role"

  pipeline_definition {
    stages = [
      {
        stage_name = "Preprocessing"
        stage_definition {
          parameters = {
            preprocessInput = {
              inputFileS3Uri = "s3://my-bucket/preprocessed-data"
            }
          }
          step = {
            name = "standardscaling",
            step_outputs = {
              CachedOutputS3Uri = {
                OutputS3Uri = "s3://my-bucket/stddev-scaled-model"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      },
      {
        stage_name = "Inference"
        stage_definition {
          parameters = {
            TransformInput = {
              ModelName = "my-trained-model"
              OutputS3Uri = "s3://my-bucket/datatest"
            }
          }
          step = {
            name = "ModelTransform"
            step_outputs = {
              TransformedOutputS3Uri = {
                OutputS3Uri = "s3://my-bucket/transformed-data"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

This configuration sets up a basic SageMaker pipeline with a "Preprocessing" stage and an "Inference" stage, defining steps and parameters for each stage. Adjustments may be needed to fit the specifics of your pipeline configuration, role ARNs, stage definitions, and parameters.

