```hcl
resource "aws_iam_group" "example" {
  name = "example-group"
}

resource "aws_iam_policy" "example_policy" {
  name        = "example-group-policy"
  description = "Example policy for example group"

  policy = jsonencode({
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
      {
        "Effect": "Allow",
        "Action": [
          "s3:ListBucket"
        ],
        "Resource": "*"
      }
    ])
}

resource "aws_iam_group_policy_attachment" "example_attachment" {
  group      = aws_iam_group.example.name
  policy_arn = aws_iam_policy.example_policy.  arn
}
```

In this configuration:

- `aws_iam_group` creates the IAM group `example-group`.
- `aws_iam_policy` defines the IAM policy with an example name and policy.
- `aws_iam_group_policy_attachment` attaches the defined policy to the IAM group using the ARN of the policy.

