Certainly! Below is the Terraform configuration for creating an S3 bucket with the bucket owner paying the object ownership costs. The configuration uses AWS provider with Terraform's HCL syntax inside a Markdown code block:

```hcl
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "example" {
  bucket = "example-bucket"
  acl    = "private"

  versioning {
    enabled = true
  }

  lifecycle {
    prevent_destroy = true
  }

  ownership_controls {
    rules = {
      ownership = "BucketOwnerPreferred"
    }
  }
}
```

In this configuration, an S3 bucket named `example-bucket` is created with ownership rules set to "BucketOwnerPreferred" to ensure the bucket owner pays for the object storage fees. Following Terraform conventions, the lifecycle block is used to prevent accidental destruction of the bucket, and versioning is enabled for completeness. Adjust the bucket name and other details as necessary to fit your specific requirements.

