To generate the Terraform configuration for an AWS service that uses API Gateway and S3 to provide a web server for uploading cat pictures and serving random cat pictures, we will set up an S3 bucket to store the cat pictures and an API Gateway to expose the S3 bucket through a web server. It will involve setting up some AWS IAM roles and policies for proper access settings.

Here's the Terraform configuration:

```hcl
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-west-1"
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket" "cat_photos" {
  bucket = "random-cat-photos-bucket"
  acl    = "private"
}

