This configuration creates an AWS VPC with public subnets using a simplified CIDR configuration (`10.0.%d.0/24`), a security group enabling access on port 5432 (PostgreSQL's default port) from the designated subnets, and a PostgreSQL RDS database named "dolphinscheduler", with version 17.1, 5GB capacity, no final snapshot, and associated with that VPC and security group. Adjust the az/availability_zone structure according to your specific needs.

