To create a Lightsail Disk resource, assign it to a LightSail Instance, and ensure it is properly configured, you can use the following Terraform configuration in HCL format:

```hcl
resource "aws_lightsail_instance" "example_instance" {
  name          = "example-instance"
  availability_zone = "us-west-1"
  blueprint_id  = "f3621a72-f8b3-3073-578c-dd40b8b3f8dc"
  bundle_id    = "3_16" // Plans for your Lightsail instance
}

resource "aws_lightsail_disk" "example_disk" {
  availability_zone = "us-west-1"
  name                = "example-disk"
  size                = 10 // GB
  attachment {
    instance_name = aws_lightsail_instance.example_instance.name
  }
}
```

This code sets up a LightSail instance and attaches a LightSail disk to it. The disk is created in the same availability zone as the instance, and specified the size of the disk. Adjust the parameters as needed for your environment (e.g., instance name, zone, disk size, and disk name).

