To facilitate the vault lock, a lifecycle rule with a transition to Glacier and server-side encryption using Amazon S3's default KMS master key is applied. In combination with a custom S3 bucket policy, you can ensure that data is automatically locked in Glacier if it is stored in the "vault" prefix of the bucket. Use AWS IAM policies to define the keys that can access the bucket and specify the actions permitted on the locked contents. This example showcases how to create a Glacier vault with automatic encryption and lifecycle transitions leveraging Amazon S3's capabilities, which might not be directly applicable to Glacier vaults but is used here for illustration purposes.

