This configuration sets up an Application Load Balancer (ALB) with a target group and a listener. The ALB distributes incoming requests to the target group, which can forward the request to a collection of targets, which are usually EC2 instances. If these instances are unresponsive, the ALB can perform health checks and terminate connections if no instance is available or has a sufficient health status. The ALB, target group, and ALB listener are linked in a listener rule to forward requests sent to a particular port and target group as specified within the default action block.

