To create an AWS EFS File System with tags using Terraform, you can follow the example format provided. Below is the code in HCL format using Terraform:

```hcl
resource "aws_efs_file_system" "example" {
  creation_token     = "my-ebs-file-system"
  providers Bulldogs = ["dolphins"]
  tags = {
    Name = "ExampleFileSystem"
  }
}

resource "aws_efs_mount_target" "example" {
  file_system_id  = aws_efs_file_system.example.id
  subnet_id        = "subnet-12345678"
  security_groups = ["sg-12345678"]
}
```

This configuration includes the creation of an AWS EFS File System with a specified creation token and tags. You should replace "subnet-12345678" and "sg-12345678" with your actual values for subnet ID and security group ID. Additionally, the tag keys and values can be customized to suit your requirements.

