Here's the Terraform configuration for creating an egress-only internet gateway associated with a specified VPC, with a tag:

```hcl
resource "aws_vpc" "main" {
  cidr_block = "10.0.0.0/16"
}

resource "aws_internet_gateway" "pike" {
  vpc_id = aws_vpc.main.id
  tags = {
    Name        = "pike"
    Permissions = "Egress Only"
  }
}
```

This HCL code creates the VPC if it isn't already defined, and initializes an egress-only internet gateway named "pike" with tagging. Adjust the `cidr_block` to match your specified VPC.

