response:
To establish a VPC peering connection between two AWS VPCs, you can use the Terraform AWS provider to configure the VPC peering connection in HCL format. Below is the Terraform configuration for this request:

```hcl
resource "aws_vpc_peering_connection" "pike" {
  vpc_id      = aws_vpc.peer.id
  peer_vpc_id = aws_vpc.base.id
  auto_accept = true

  tags = {
    Name = "Pike"
  }
}

resource "aws_vpc" "peer" {
  cidr_block = "10.0.0.0/24"
}

resource "aws_vpc" "base" {
  cidr_block = "10.1.0.0/24"
}
```

In this code block, the VPC peering connection named "Pike" is configured between two VPCs, "peer" and "base," with their respective CIDR blocks. The `auto_accept` attribute can be specified on either side of the peering connection to enable automatic acceptance of the peering request by the peer VPC. Adjust the configuration to match your specific environment where you might need to set `auto_accept` on the other side as well, or use it manually outside Terraform.

